          "19": "The case-crossover design controls time-invariant confounding but is susceptible to exposure-time-trend bias if exposure prevalence changes over time (mitigated by referent selection / the CCTC variant); it assumes transient exposure and abrupt outcome onset; outcome misclassification is possible.",
          "21": "Results generalise to the source populations of the contributing AsPEN databases: " + sitesPlain + ".",
